  "text": "HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 Header Translation in Envoy v1.31.2\n\n## Overview\nEnvoy's HTTP/1.1 codec handles the translation of HTTP/1.1 headers into HTTP/2 format through a combination of parsing, normalization, and pseudo-header injection. This process occurs in the source/common/http/http1/ directory.\n\n## Header Case Normalization (Lowercase Conversion)\n\nThe primary header normalization occurs in **source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc** in the `ConnectionImpl::completeCurrentHeader()` function (around line 568):\n\n```cpp\ncurrent_header_field_.inlineTransform([](char c) { return absl::ascii_tolower(c); });\n```\n\nThis converts all incoming HTTP/1.1 header names to lowercase before they are stored in the header map. This is essential for HTTP/2 compliance, as all header names in HTTP/2 MUST be lowercase per RFC 7540.\n\n## Pseudo-Header Injection\n\nPseudo-headers are injected during header processing in **source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc** in the `ServerConnectionImpl::onHeadersCompleteBase()` function (lines 1201-1266):\n\n1. **:method** (line 1233):\n   - `headers->setMethod(parser_->methodName());`\n   - Extracted from the HTTP/1.1 request line (GET, POST, CONNECT, etc.)\n   - Set directly as a pseudo-header\n\n2. **:path** (line 1174 in handlePath):\n   - `headers.setPath(absolute_url.pathAndQueryParams());`\n   - Extracted from the request-target in the request line\n   - Handles both absolute-form and origin-form URLs\n\n3. **:scheme** (line 1160 in handlePath):\n   - `headers.setScheme(absl::AsciiStrToLower(absolute_url.scheme()));`\n   - Extracted from absolute-form URLs or inferred from connection type (http/https)\n   - Lowercased for HTTP/2 compliance\n\n4. **:authority** (line 1156 in handlePath):\n   - `headers.setHost(absolute_url.hostAndPort());`\n   - Set from the absolute-form URL's host and port or from the Host header\n   - Replaces or validates the Host header as per RFC 7230\n\n## Upgrade Header Handling\n\nUpgrade header processing occurs in **source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc** in `ConnectionImpl::onHeadersCompleteImpl()` (lines 855-885):\n\n- Detects Upgrade and Connection headers\n- Handles HTTP/2 Cleartext (h2c) upgrade requests (currently removed)\n- Processes WebSocket and other upgrade requests\n- Sets the `handling_upgrade_` flag to enter upgrade mode\n- Special handling for CONNECT method (treated as upgrade)\n\n## Processing Pipeline\n\n### 1. Parsing Phase\n**source/common/http/http1/balsa_parser.cc**:\n- `BalsaParser::execute()` - Main parsing entry point\n- `BalsaParser::OnRequestFirstLineInput()` - Parses request line (method, URI, version)\n- `BalsaParser::validateAndProcessHeadersOrTrailersImpl()` - Processes individual headers\n- Validates header names and values according to RFC specifications\n\n### 2. Header Field/Value Accumulation\n**source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc**:\n- `ConnectionImpl::onHeaderFieldImpl()` - Accumulates header field name\n- `ConnectionImpl::onHeaderValueImpl()` - Accumulates header field value\n- Handles whitespace trimming per RFC 7230\n\n### 3. Header Completion and Normalization\n**source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc**, `ConnectionImpl::completeCurrentHeader()`:\n- Applies stateful formatter for header case preservation (if configured)\n- Normalizes header name to lowercase using `inlineTransform()`\n- Validates header name contains no underscore characters (if required)\n- Adds header to the header map via `addViaMove()`\n\n### 4. Header Map Storage\n**source/common/http/header_map_impl.cc**:\n- `HeaderMapImpl::addReferenceKey()` - Adds header with lowercase key\n- Headers are stored with `LowerCaseString` keys for case-insensitive lookup\n- Pseudo-headers are distinguished by leading colon in the name\n\n### 5. Pseudo-Header Finalization\n**source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc**, `ServerConnectionImpl::onHeadersCompleteBase()`:\n- Handles URL parsing and scheme validation\n- Injects :method, :path, :scheme, :authority pseudo-headers\n- Validates that the resulting header set is valid for HTTP/2\n- Calls `HeaderUtility::requestHeadersValid()` to verify RFC compliance\n\n## Header Formatter Integration\n\n**source/common/http/http1/header_formatter.cc** and **source/common/http/http1/header_formatter.h**:\n- Provides `ProperCaseHeaderKeyFormatter` for optional header case formatting\n- Allows Envoy to preserve or format header names during encoding\n- Applied during stateful formatting in `completeCurrentHeader()` (line 566)\n- The formatter is called with the original header name before lowercasing\n\n## Key Constants and Definitions\n\n**source/common/http/headers.h**:\n- Defines pseudo-header names: `:method`, `:path`, `:scheme`, `:authority`, `:protocol`\n- Defines standard HTTP/1.1 headers and their HTTP/2 equivalents\n- Method values (GET, POST, CONNECT, HEAD, etc.)\n- Scheme values (http, https)\n\n## Connection Upgrade Detection\n\nUpgrade handling in **source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc** (lines 855-885):\n- Checks for Upgrade and Connection headers\n- Detects h2c (HTTP/2 Cleartext) and other upgrade types\n- For h2c: removes unsupported upgrade headers\n- For CONNECT: automatically enters upgrade mode\n- Uses helper function `caseUnorderedSetContainingUpgradeAndHttp2Settings()` for case-insensitive header comparison\n\nThis comprehensive header translation system ensures that HTTP/1.1 requests are properly converted to HTTP/2-compliant headers with all required pseudo-headers, proper case normalization, and correct upgrade handling."
}

